## bb5 Command Shortcuts

### My Aliases
| Alias | Expands To | When to Use |
|-------|------------|-------------|
| `bb5 here` | `bb5 whereami` | Quick context check |
| `bb5 next` | `bb5 task:list --status=pending --limit=5` | See next tasks |
| `bb5 current` | `bb5 task:current` | What am I working on? |
| `bb5 recent` | `bb5 runs:list --limit=10` | Recent activity |
| `bb5 done` | `bb5 task:complete --with-learnings` | Finish current task |
| `bb5 todo` | `bb5 task:create --template=quick` | Quick task creation |

### Default Flags
- Always use `--with-context` for task creation
- Default sort: priority desc, created asc
- Show task IDs in all lists

---

## Workflow Preferences

### Task Handling
- Auto-claim: Yes, when task is clear and <2 hours
- Auto-create runs: Yes, always create run folder
- Default commit message format: `type(scope): description`

### Documentation Style
- LEARNINGS.md: Required for every run
- DECISIONS.md: When choosing between >2 options
- ASSUMPTIONS.md: Stream of consciousness, don't polish
- RESULTS.md: Bullet points, not prose

### Commit Preferences
```
type(scope): description

- Detail 1
- Detail 2

Task: TASK-XXX
```

Types: feat, fix, docs, refactor, test, chore
Always include: Task ID, Co-authored-by line

---

## Modified Stop Conditions

### Additional Stop Triggers
- Estimated time >4 hours
- Touching >5 files in critical path
- Changing files I didn't author
- Task description <10 words (clarify first)

### Skip Confirmation For
- Adding tests (even to production code)
- Documentation improvements
- Refactoring with tests in place
- Config updates (non-production)
- File reads and searches

---

## Testing Approach

### Always Write Tests For
- New features
- Bug fixes (regression test)
- Public APIs
- Complex logic (>10 lines)

### Test Style
- Arrange-Act-Assert comments
- Descriptive test names: `should_X_when_Y`
- One assertion per test (preferably)

### Skip Tests For
- Simple getters/setters
- Config files
- Type definitions
- Obvious glue code

---

## Context Management

### At 70% Usage
- Summarize THOUGHTS.md (keep last 10 entries)
- Keep all DECISIONS.md and ASSUMPTIONS.md
- Preserve current task objective

### At 85% Usage
- Complete current subtask
- Exit with PARTIAL status
- Document exact next steps

### What to Preserve
- Current task objective
- Recent decisions (last 5)
- Open questions
- Blockers

---

## Notification Preferences

### Tell Me About
- Task completion (1 line summary)
- Blockers (immediate)
- Unexpected errors (with context)
- Context rollover (brief notice)
- Agent switches

### Don't Tell Me About
- Individual file reads
- Successful tool calls
- Normal workflow steps
- Cache hits

### Progress Updates
- Every 30 minutes for long tasks
- At completion of each subtask
- When switching agents

